{
  "texts": [
    "As he observed back then: 'Computers were powerful, but also mysterious.",
    "Their power was ours to use, but not to understand.",
    "When technology is a black box, it becomes magical' [39 p.252].",
    "Second conceptual issue: the myth of the uncontrollability of AIThe first conceptual issue is connected to the second one: the belief that the development of AI is getting out of control.",
    "As Nyholm [52] notes, 'whenever there is talk about any form of AI or new technologies more generally, worries about control tend to come up.'"
  ]
}